"\"center\"/> apparirà un menu a discesa."

#: ../build/doc/usermanual/po/darktable-usermanual_profiled.xml:17876(para)
msgid ""
"The idea behind this mask is to create smooth transitions between tonal "
"ranges, so as to avoid creating halos. Yet, the mask is also able to create "
"well defined edges for high contrast areas of the image. Having this mask "
"displayed will assist in understanding the follow parameters:"
msgstr ""

#: ../build/doc/usermanual/po/darktable-usermanual_profiled.xml:17886(title)
msgid "preserve details mode"
msgstr ""

#: ../build/doc/usermanual/po/darktable-usermanual_profiled.xml:17888(para)
msgid ""
"There are several different filters that can be used to smooth the mask. If "
"preserve details is disabled, the mask is not smoothed. Guided filter blurs "
"the mask smoothing more shadows than highlights, which is sometimes "
"desirable if you lighten the shadows a lot, but may result in loss of local "
"contrast in highlights if you darken them. Eigf blurs the mask in a way that "
"is independent from exposure: highlights and shadows will be blurred more "
"uniformly. Guided filter averaged and eigf averaged will perform the "
"geometric mean of the result of the filter and the original mask: details "
"will not be as preserved as without the average, but the averaging will "
"reduce halos."
msgstr ""

#: ../build/doc/usermanual/po/darktable-usermanual_profiled.xml:17901(para)
#: ../build/doc/usermanual/po/darktable-usermanual_profiled.xml:17918(para)
msgid ""
"If you increase this to 2, a second mask is calculated using the first mask "
"as an input. As a result, the new mask is more fuzzy than when there was "
"only one instance of the mask. Progressively higher values will diffuse the "
"mask even further."
msgstr ""

#: ../build/doc/usermanual/po/darktable-usermanual_profiled.xml:17911(title)
#, fuzzy
msgid "filter diffusion"
msgstr "filtraggio"

#: ../build/doc/usermanual/po/darktable-usermanual_profiled.xml:17913(para)
msgid ""
"This defaults to a value of 1, meaning there is one instance of the mask "
"generated."
msgstr ""

#: ../build/doc/usermanual/po/darktable-usermanual_profiled.xml:17928(title)
msgid "smoothing diameter"
msgstr ""

#: ../build/doc/usermanual/po/darktable-usermanual_profiled.xml:17930(para)
msgid ""
"With lower values, the transition between dark areas of the mask and lighter "
"areas of the mask will be more pronounced. As this value is increased, those "
"transitions become smoother/softer."
msgstr ""

#: ../build/doc/usermanual/po/darktable-usermanual_profiled.xml:17939(title)
msgid "edge refinement/feathering"
msgstr ""

#: ../build/doc/usermanual/po/darktable-usermanual_profiled.xml:17941(para)
msgid ""
"Higher values will force the mask to follow high contrast edges more "
"closely. Lower values will give smoother gradients, but may introduce some "
"halos."
msgstr ""

#: ../build/doc/usermanual/po/darktable-usermanual_profiled.xml:17952(title)
#, fuzzy
msgid "Compress shadows/highlights presets"
msgstr "colore ombre e alte luci"

#: ../build/doc/usermanual/po/darktable-usermanual_profiled.xml:17954(para)
msgid ""
"The module comes with several presets to compress shadows and highlights. "
"For each of these presets, 2 variants are proposed, one with guided filter "
"(gf) and one with exposure independent guided filter (eigf). Depending on "
"the image, one or the other may give better results. In both case, these "
"presets preserve middle-grey so that you do not have to adjust global "
"exposure before and after toneequalizer."
msgstr ""

#: ../build/doc/usermanual/po/darktable-usermanual_profiled.xml:17970(title)
msgid "Tonemapping"
msgstr "Mappatura dei toni"

#: ../build/doc/usermanual/po/darktable-usermanual_profiled.xml:17974(secondary)
#: ../build/doc/usermanual/po/darktable-usermanual_profiled.xml:17978(primary)
msgid "tonemapping"
msgstr "toni, mappatura"

#: ../build/doc/usermanual/po/darktable-usermanual_profiled.xml:17992(entry)
msgid ""
"This module compresses the tonal range of HDR images, so they fit into the "
"limits of a normal, low dynamic range image, using Durand's 2002 algorithm. "
"darktable can import HDR images if they come in OpenEXR, RGBE or PFM format "
"or as a DNG generated by darktable's HDR creation mechanism (see <xref "
"linkend=\"selected_images\"/>)."
msgstr ""
"Questo modulo comprime la gamma tonale di un'immagine HDR per farla "
"rientrare nei limiti di una normale gamma dinamica utilizzando l'algoritmo "
"Durand 2002. darktable può importare immagini HDR nei formati OpenEXR, RGBE "
"o PMF oppure in formato DNG che è quello generato dal sistema interno di "
"darktable per la creazione di immagini HDR (vedi <xref linkend="
"\"selected_images\"/>)."

#: ../build/doc/usermanual/po/darktable-usermanual_profiled.xml:18013(para)
msgid ""
"The underlying algorithm uses a bilateral filter to decompose an image into "
"a coarse base layer and a detail layer. The contrast of the base layer is "
"compressed, while the detail layer is preserved, then both layers are re-"
"combined."
msgstr ""
"L'algoritmo sottostante usa un filtro bilaterale per scomporre l'immagine in "
"layer di base grezzo e uno dettagliato. Il contrasto del livello base viene "
"compresso mentre quello del livello dettagliato non viene modificato: fatto "
"questo i due livelli vengono nuovamente fusi."

#: ../build/doc/usermanual/po/darktable-usermanual_profiled.xml:18020(title)
msgid "contrast compression"
msgstr "compressione contrasto"

#: ../build/doc/usermanual/po/darktable-usermanual_profiled.xml:18021(para)
msgid ""
"Sets the contrast compression level of the base layer. A higher compression "
"will make the image fit a lower dynamic range."
msgstr ""
"Imposta il livello di compressione del livello di base. Una più alta "
"compressione renderà possibile fare rientrare l'immagine in una gamma "
"dinamica più piccola."

#: ../build/doc/usermanual/po/darktable-usermanual_profiled.xml:18029(para)
msgid ""
"Sets the spatial extent of the bilateral filter. Lower values cause the "
"contrast compression to have stronger effects on image details."
msgstr ""
"Imposta l'estensione spaziale del filtro bilaterale. Valori più bassi "
"aumentano la compressione del contrasto e hanno un impatto maggiore sui "
"dettagli dell'immagine."

#: ../build/doc/usermanual/po/darktable-usermanual_profiled.xml:18045(secondary)
#: ../build/doc/usermanual/po/darktable-usermanual_profiled.xml:18049(primary)
msgid "white balance"
msgstr "bilanciamento del bianco"

#: ../build/doc/usermanual/po/darktable-usermanual_profiled.xml:18062(entry)
msgid ""
"This module is used to set the white balance. You have three ways to "
"interact with it: (a) Set up tint and temperature, (b) define the value of "
"each channel, or (c) choose from predefined white balances."
msgstr ""
"Questo modulo è usato per impostare il bilanciamento del bianco. Potete "
"interagire con esso in tre modi: (a) Impostare tinta e temperatura, (b) "
"definire il valore di ogni canale oppure (c) selezionare un bilanciamento "
"predefinito."

#: ../build/doc/usermanual/po/darktable-usermanual_profiled.xml:18082(title)
msgid "tint"
msgstr "tinta"

#: ../build/doc/usermanual/po/darktable-usermanual_profiled.xml:18083(para)
msgid ""
"Alter the color tint of the image, from magenta (value &lt; 1) to green "
"(value &gt; 1). The channel sliders will be updated when you adjust this "
"parameter."
msgstr ""
"Modifica il colore della tinta dell'immagine dal magenta (valore &lt; 1) al "
"verde (valore &gt; 1). Il selettore scorrevole del canale verrà modificato "
"nel momento in cui regolate questo parametro."

#: ../build/doc/usermanual/po/darktable-usermanual_profiled.xml:18090(title)
msgid "temperature"
msgstr "temperatura"

#: ../build/doc/usermanual/po/darktable-usermanual_profiled.xml:18091(para)
msgid ""
"Set the color temperature (in Kelvin). The channel sliders will be updated "
"when you adjust this parameter. darktable derives the color temperature from "
"the Exif data using some model assumptions. The value given is not meant to "
"be authoritative. In the end only the updated channel values determine how "
"the image is modified."
msgstr ""
"Imposta la temperatura colore (in gradi Kelvin). I selettori scorrevoli dei "
"canali verranno modificati quando andrete ad intervenire su questo "
"parametro. darktable ricava il colore della temperatura dei dati Exif "
"utilizzando alcuni modelli. Il valore proposto non è autorevole: in fondo "
"solo i valori dei vari canali determineranno il risultato sull'immagine."

#: ../build/doc/usermanual/po/darktable-usermanual_profiled.xml:18100(title)
msgid "red, green and blue channels"
msgstr "canali rosso, verde e blu"

#: ../build/doc/usermanual/po/darktable-usermanual_profiled.xml:18101(para)
msgid "Set the channel values on a scale from 0 to 8."
msgstr "Imposta il valore dei canali su una scala da 0 a 8."

#: ../build/doc/usermanual/po/darktable-usermanual_profiled.xml:18107(title)
msgid "preset"
msgstr "preset"

#: ../build/doc/usermanual/po/darktable-usermanual_profiled.xml:18108(para)
msgid ""
"Select a preset white balance. <informaltable frame=\"none\" width=\"80%"
"\"><tgroup cols=\"2\" colsep=\"0\" rowsep=\"0\"><colspec colwidth=\"4*\"/"
"><colspec colwidth=\"6*\"/><tbody><row><entry><emphasis>camera white balance "
"(default)</emphasis></entry><entry> White balance reported by the camera. </"
"entry></row><row><entry><emphasis>camera neutral</emphasis></entry><entry> "
"Essentially sets temperature to 6502K. The actual math: it computes such "
"white balance channel multipliers, so that pure white color in camera "
"colorspace is converted into pure white color in sRGB D65. (pure white color "
"here means having the same equal value for each channel = 1.0) </entry></"
"row><row><entry><emphasis>spot white balance</emphasis></entry><entry> "
"Select a square area in your image containing mostly grey pixels. The white "
"balance is calculated based on the selected area. </entry></"
"row><row><entry><emphasis>camera presets</emphasis></entry><entry> Camera "
"specific white balance presets. Examples: direct sunlight, flash, cloudy, "
"shade and a number of indoor lighting options. </entry></row></tbody></"
"tgroup></informaltable>"
msgstr ""
"Seleziona un bilanciamento del bianco preimpostato. <informaltable frame="
"\"none\" width=\"80%\"><tgroup cols=\"2\" colsep=\"0\" rowsep=\"0\"><colspec "
"colwidth=\"4*\"/><colspec colwidth=\"6*\"/"
"><tbody><row><entry><emphasis>Fotocamera (predefinito)</emphasis></"
"entry><entry> Bilanciamento come riportato dalla fotocamera. </entry></"
"row><row><entry><emphasis>Fotocamera neutrale</emphasis></entry><entry> "
"Fondamentalmente imposta la temperatura a 6502K con questo calcolo "
"matematico: imposta il livello di bianco in modo che il bianco puro "
"registrato dalla fotocamera venga convertito in bianco puro sRGB D65 (bianco "
"puro significa che ogni canale ha un valore uguale a 1.0) </entry></"
"row><row><entry><emphasis>Punto</emphasis></entry><entry> Seleziona un'area "
"dell'immagine che contiene soprattutto pixel grigi. Il bilanciamento del "
"bianco viene calcolato sulla base dell'area selezionata. </entry></"
"row><row><entry><emphasis>preset fotocamera</emphasis></entry><entry>, una "
"serie di bilanciamenti  pre-configurati. Esempio: luce solare diretta, "
"flash, nuvoloso, ombra oltre ad un a certa quantità di opzioni per la luce "
"artificiale. </entry></row></tbody></tgroup></informaltable>"

#: ../build/doc/usermanual/po/darktable-usermanual_profiled.xml:18159(title)
msgid "finetune"
msgstr "regolazione fine"

#: ../build/doc/usermanual/po/darktable-usermanual_profiled.xml:18160(para)
msgid ""
"Some cameras offer additional finetuning parameters if one of the camera "
"presets is selected. Depending on camera white balance, can be adjusted in "
"steps within a certain range. The adjustments are usually towards yellow "
"(value &lt; 1) or blue (value &gt; 1)."
msgstr ""
"Alcune fotocamere mettono a disposizione altri parametri per una regolazione "
"accurata nel caso in cui venga selezionato un preset direttamente in camera. "
"Il bilanciamento del bianco della fotocamera può quindi essere ulteriormente "
"regolato entro certi valori. Questi aggiustamenti tendono solitamente al "
"giallo (valori &lt; 1) oppure al blu (valori &gt; 1)."

#: ../build/doc/usermanual/po/darktable-usermanual_profiled.xml:18168(title)
msgid "Notes"
msgstr ""

#: ../build/doc/usermanual/po/darktable-usermanual_profiled.xml:18169(para)
msgid ""
"The history in the database and associated XMP file, and in a style, does "
"not contain the temperature and tint. Instead it holds values related to the "
"three RGB coefficients which can be set in the white balance module. The "
"relationship between these two sets of values - RGB and temp/tint - depends "
"on camera characteristics. Therefore applying white balance in a style made "
"with one camera model to another camera model will in general give a "
"different temp/tint, and your image might look different to what you "
"expected. Consider doing all white balancing explicitly in the module."
msgstr ""

#: ../build/doc/usermanual/po/darktable-usermanual_profiled.xml:18182(para)
msgid ""
"The mathematical relationship between the two sets of values is not "
"straightforward. Colour balances can be set using the RGB sliders which have "
"no corresponding setting in terms of temperature and tint (this mainly "
"happens when very high temperature values are calculated from the slider "
"values). Therefore be aware that editing white balance using temp/tint on an "
"image previously made using the RGB sliders may give odd results, at least "
"if high temperature values are involved."
msgstr ""

#: ../build/doc/usermanual/po/darktable-usermanual_profiled.xml:18202(title)
